caption: One of a handful of cafe lined squares in Bordeaux. In addition to the eateries, cannele speciality shops and other retails shops there is a peculiar monument of what appear to be Roman era column and capital. It is a nice square.
Nice square, good atmosphere, and plenty of places for a bite to eat and drink.
Stopped by here for a lunch, nice atmosphere in the centre, lots of restaurants, cafe and shops around.

Lively and atmospheric square with good quality bars, restaurants and boutiques. Street arts and entertainment attract a cosmopolitan crowd of all ages. A relaxed atmosphere encourages you to linger and enjoy the ambience.
Very good mussels with flawless service in the heart of Bordeaux.
Lovely wee square to wander through. Various markets in through the week and nice bars and restaurants around the sides.
Really nice plaza with lots of restaurants to choose from, really nice to sit and people watch in while enjoying some local wine.

Wonderful place with the best restaurants in town to have food at any time of the day. The atmosphere is so special and beautiful. You have a variety of restaurants with French food as well as Italian and standard salads, burgers,... You also can have only a beer there, if the weather is good, it's definitely the place to be!
